%N A093821 Decimal expansion of (2*(3 - sqrt(3)))/3.
%C A093821 Area of lamina found by Pal in the Lebesgue minimal problem.
%C A093821 This appears also as the ratio r_3/r_4 of the outer radii of a regular triangle circumscribed by a regular quadrangle such that they share one vertex and the other two vertices of the triangle touch two sides of the quadrangle. The center of the quadrangle is displaced from the center of the triangle by d/r_4 = 1-2/sqrt(3) = 0.154700.. (see A020832). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 22 2013
%H A093821 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/LebesgueMinimalProblem.html">Lebesgue Minimal Problem</a>.
%H A093821 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_02">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 2</a>.
%F A093821 Minimal polynomial: 3*x^2 - 12*x + 8. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 19 2026
%e A093821 0.84529946162074847098170243899608508870479649745974...
%p A093821 evalf(2*(1-1/sqrt(3))) ; # _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 22 2013
